Path: godot/classes/class_skeletonmodification2d.rst
Summary: This section details the methods available for the SkeletonModification2D class in Godot Engine.

Method: _draw_editor_gizmo() → void
This method is a virtual function used for drawing editor gizmos.

Method: _execute(delta: float) → void
This method is a virtual function that executes the modification logic, taking the frame delta as an argument.

Method: _setup_modification(modification_stack: SkeletonModificationStack2D) → void
This method is a virtual function used to set up the modification, receiving the SkeletonModificationStack2D as a parameter.

Method: clamp_angle(angle: float, min: float, max: float, invert: bool) → float
Clamps an angle between a minimum and maximum value. The `invert` parameter allows for reversing the clamping direction.

Method: get_editor_draw_gizmo() → bool
Returns whether the editor gizmo should be drawn for this modification.

Method: get_is_setup() → bool
Returns whether the modification has been set up.

Method: get_modification_stack() → SkeletonModificationStack2D
Returns the SkeletonModificationStack2D that this modification belongs to.

Method: set_editor_draw_gizmo(draw_gizmo: bool) → void
Sets whether the editor gizmo should be drawn for this modification.

Method: set_is_setup(is_setup: bool) → void
Sets whether the modification is considered set up.
