Document: SkeletonModification2D
Path: godot/classes/class_skeletonmodification2d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the SkeletonModification2D class, including enabling modifications and their execution modes.

Property: enabled (bool)
Description: If true, the modification's _execute() function will be called by the SkeletonModificationStack2D.
Default: true
Setget: set_enabled(value: bool), get_enabled() → bool

Property: execution_mode (int)
Description: The execution mode for the modification. This tells the modification stack when to execute the modification. Some modifications have settings that are only available in certain execution modes.
Default: 0
Setget: set_execution_mode(value: int), get_execution_mode() → int
